        <h3 class="node-title article__title--card">
            <a href="/news/core-score-wall-street-journal" rel="bookmark"><span class='field-wrapper article__title article__title--card'>CORE Score in the Wall Street Journal</span></a>
        </h3>
        <div class="article__teaser article__teaser--card field field-node--field-teaser-plain field-name-field-teaser-plain field-type-string-long field-label-hidden">
    <div class="field-items">
          <div class="field-item">A Wall Street Journal essay features the CORE Score, a metric created by the Academy&#039;s Commission on Reimagining the Economy to help move national focus from how the economy is doing to how Americans are doing. In this essay, the CORE Score helps explain how standard economic measures may indicate a good economy, while that&#039;s not what many Americans are feeling about their own wellbeing. </div>
      </div>
</div>

